          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1704298030674-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1704298030674-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the sausages are cooked through, remove the tray[s] from the oven, add the<strong> hoisin glaze </strong>and your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame seeds</strong> (reserve the bowl), then give everything a good mix up then return the tray[s] to the oven for 5-7 min further or until sticky and caramelised – this is your <strong>sticky hoisin sausage traybake</strong></p><p>Wipe the reserved bowl clean and add the <strong>remaining sriracha </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!) with your <strong>mayo </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> – this is your<strong> sriracha mayo</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
